│ THOUGHT: My fix is still causing test failures. The issue is that I'm allowing plans with scalar VF to proceed even when `adjustFixedOrderRecurrences` fails. But these plans might also have vector VFs, and  │
│ `adjustFixedOrderRecurrences` is needed for vectorization.                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The problem is that a plan can have both scalar and vector VFs. My check `Plan->hasVF(ElementCount::getFixed(1))` returns true if the plan has VF=1, even if it also has other VFs. So when                    │
│ `adjustFixedOrderRecurrences` fails for a plan that has VF=1 and VF=4, we're still proceeding, which breaks vectorization.                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ I need to check if the plan has ONLY scalar VF (VF=1 and no other VFs). Let me fix this.                                                                                                                       │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ cd /llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm && sed -i '9228,9232c\  // If the plan includes scalar VF=1 and adjustFixedOrderRecurrences fails,\n  // we can still proceed as scalar loops don'\''t need this               │
│ transformation.\n  // But only if the plan has ONLY scalar VF (not also vector VFs).\n  bool HasOnlyScalarVF = Plan->hasVF(ElementCount::getFixed(1)) &&\n                         size(Plan->vectorFactors()) │
│ == 1;\n  if (!VPlanTransforms::adjustFixedOrderRecurrences(*Plan, Builder)) {\n    if (!HasOnlyScalarVF)\n      return nullptr;\n    LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "LV: adjustFixedOrderRecurrences failed for plan     │
│ with only scalar VF, continuing anyway.\\n");\n  }' ./llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp                                                                                                          │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                                            │
